article.headline: Bradley 72, Evansville 71
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Will Franklin scored 12 points and made a free throw with one second left to give Bradley a 72-71 victory over Evansville on Wednesday. Bradley (18-10, 9-7 Missouri Valley Conference) shot 10-of-17 (59 percent) from behind the arc in the first half and led 42-27 at halftime. Evansville's Matt Webster hit a 3-pointer with seven seconds remaining to tie the game at 71-71, but Shy Ely fouled Franklin with one second left to set up his winning free throw. Franklin finished with 12 points and Jeremy Crouch had 15 points to lead the Braves. Webster led the Purple Aces (13-14, 6-10) with 19 points and seven rebounds but had five turnovers. Evansville committed 13 turnovers which the Braves turned into 18 points.
